# .cursorrules — Another Agent Skills (Cursor Adapter)

This project uses Another Agent Skills — a production-grade skill framework.
Skills are installed at ~/.config/opencode/skills/ (or $AGENT_SKILLS_DIR/skills/). Load the matching skill before coding.

## Skill Reference

- frontend-web: Web UI (React/Next.js/Vue/Svelte)
- frontend-mobile: Mobile apps (React Native/Flutter)
- frontend-desktop: Desktop apps (Tauri/Electron)
- frontend-pwa: PWA / offline-first web apps
- backend-api-mastery: API design, databases, auth
- spec-driven-development: Requirements, specifications
- architecture-analysis: Stack and pattern decisions
- git-init-and-versioning: Git setup, branching, commits
- fullstack-shipping: CI/CD, deployment, monitoring
- project-health-check: Codebase audits
- dev-environment-audit: Tool and runtime verification
- multi-agent-orchestration: Parallel/pipeline agent patterns

## Behavioral Rules

1. Think Before Coding — State assumptions before implementing.
2. Simplicity First — Minimum viable code. No over-engineering.
3. Surgical Changes — Only touch files relevant to the request.
4. Goal-Driven Execution — Define done criteria before starting. Verify after finishing.
5. Contract Before Code — SPEC.md, DESIGN.md, .gitignore must exist first.
6. Approval Gate — No commits or pushes without explicit user approval.

## Verification Checklist

Before declaring done:
- [ ] Matching skill was loaded and followed
- [ ] Required docs (specs, design tokens) exist
- [ ] .gitignore covers the stack
- [ ] No secrets in code or commit
- [ ] Build/run succeeds
- [ ] Changes are minimal and trace to the request
